OL,3,CWhere UK weather warnings are in place
OL,4,Cahead of thunderstorms
OL,6,FWarnings for rain and thunderstorms
OL,7,Fhave been issued for parts of the UK
OL,8,Fafter the hottest temperatures of the
OL,9,Fyear so far were recorded over the
OL,10,Fweekend.
OL,12,Fbut Met Office forecasters have
OL,13,Fpredicted a week of milder
OL,14,Ftemperatures, with thunderstorms
OL,15,Fexpected to bring an an end to the
OL,16,Ffine weather enjoyed by many.
OL,18,FChertsey in Surrey recorded the
OL,19,Fwarmest temperature of 27.5C on Sunday
OL,20,Fwhile 25.3C was recorded in Usk in
OL,21,FSouth Wales, the Met Office said.
